4.1.1 Separation rates and reasons for divorce in Swaziland

Almost half of Swazi couples consider the marriage union as useful after the formation of the family (SAG/UNICEF, 2009) but over 25% of Swazi women agree separating their family unit is a feasible option. When women get married, they move into extended family sets of at least 8 people. This accounting for the fact that those who have been in permanent relationships, have had multiple divorces or marital separations (SAG/UNICEF, 2009).

One in four respondents said the reason for separation in Swaziland has been due to domestic violence1. In cases of domestic violence between partners, female victims tend to seek advice from other older women to conduct mentally healthy negotiations and reconcile; however, most of the time the husband disables the reconciliation (SAG/ UNICEF, 2009).
